WEBVTT

00:02.290 --> 00:04.540
Dre: I was 12 going on 13

00:04.540 --> 00:07.460
the first time
 I saw a dead human being.

00:07.460 --> 00:09.790
I was also 12 going on 13

00:09.790 --> 00:12.170
the second time
 I saw a dead human being.

00:12.170 --> 00:14.670
I was 13 going on 14 --

00:14.670 --> 00:16.670
Anyway, you get it.
 I saw some stuff.

00:16.670 --> 00:17.960
But that's the thing

00:17.960 --> 00:19.960
when you grow up
 in a situation like that.

00:19.960 --> 00:21.710
It makes you closer
 to the people

00:21.710 --> 00:23.830
you're living through it with,
 your crew.

00:23.830 --> 00:25.290
My boy Sha --

00:25.290 --> 00:27.710
lover of carbs,
 destroyer of property.

00:27.710 --> 00:30.040
Ronnie was the athlete
 of the crew.

00:30.040 --> 00:32.960
T Will was our ladies man.

00:32.960 --> 00:35.540
Ledarius was the wild card.

00:35.540 --> 00:36.920
And Tony --

00:36.920 --> 00:39.580
Tony was the glue,
 the peacemaker,

00:39.580 --> 00:42.580
always wanted everybody
 to be cool.

00:42.580 --> 00:45.960
In those days, you think
you're gonna be a crew forever.

00:45.960 --> 00:48.380
But then you grow up,
 you lose touch,

00:48.380 --> 00:50.460
and the calls
 come less and less

00:50.460 --> 00:54.080
until one day, you get the call
that you never want to hear.

00:54.080 --> 00:56.040
Tony's dead.

00:56.040 --> 00:58.380
What?

00:58.380 --> 01:01.920
That's two double-doubles,
two fries, and two Cokes.

01:01.920 --> 01:03.620
Need anything else?

01:03.620 --> 01:05.290
[ Voice breaking ]
A couple more double-doubles.

01:05.290 --> 01:07.330
[ Voice breaking ]
And...fries, please?

01:07.330 --> 01:09.040
And a couple
more shakes.

01:09.040 --> 01:10.540
[ Sobbing ]
Chocolate, please.

01:10.540 --> 01:11.620
Not Tony!

01:11.620 --> 01:14.210
♪♪

01:19.210 --> 01:22.880
Man. I can't believe
Tony's gone.

01:22.880 --> 01:24.290
I'm sick
of all this violence.

01:24.290 --> 01:25.710
What violence?
He died in his sleep.

01:25.710 --> 01:27.120
They shot him
while he was sleeping?

01:27.120 --> 01:28.330
Savages!

01:28.330 --> 01:30.620
No, man, he went to sleep
and just didn't wake up.

01:30.620 --> 01:34.040
That can happen?
That's a thing?

01:34.040 --> 01:36.290
I sleep...
every night, man.

01:36.290 --> 01:37.790
Hell, sometimes,
during the day.

01:37.790 --> 01:39.540
Look, his mom said
the funeral's Saturday,

01:39.540 --> 01:41.250
and we're gonna chip in
for some flowers.

01:41.250 --> 01:43.460
It's like
$35 I guess, so...

01:43.460 --> 01:45.830
so it'll be $7 apiece.

01:45.830 --> 01:47.620
What kind
of funeral flowers can --

01:47.620 --> 01:49.500
You know what?
Don't worry about it.

01:49.500 --> 01:50.250
I'll get them.

01:50.250 --> 01:51.250
Really?
 Yeah.

01:51.250 --> 01:52.620
That's dope.

01:52.620 --> 01:54.460
It's been a while since you've
seen everybody, anyway.

01:54.460 --> 01:55.380
I know.

01:55.380 --> 01:57.000
Eating your feelings.

01:57.000 --> 01:59.500
Classic stage one --
denial.

01:59.500 --> 02:01.380
This is
not the time, son.

02:01.380 --> 02:04.830
Okay, skipping right
to stage two -- anger.

02:04.830 --> 02:06.880
I don't know if you know this,
but I'm going for

02:06.880 --> 02:09.289
my peer-counseling certification
at school.

02:09.289 --> 02:11.620
Of all the people,
why would you test me?

02:11.620 --> 02:13.170
Come on, Dad.

02:13.170 --> 02:15.040
I need you
to share your pain

02:15.040 --> 02:16.420
and sign my grief log.

02:16.420 --> 02:18.080
10 hours
of hands-on training,

02:18.080 --> 02:20.620
and I can walk into any YMCA
in the world

02:20.620 --> 02:22.120
and set up shizz-op.

02:22.120 --> 02:25.620
Sports, girls, drugs --

02:25.620 --> 02:26.960
None of this
interests you, huh?

02:28.500 --> 02:29.960
[ Grunts ]
 Okay, okay.

02:32.670 --> 02:34.830
Death can be hard
to understand.

02:34.830 --> 02:37.330
Sorry about
your friend Tommy.

02:37.330 --> 02:38.710
Tony.

02:40.170 --> 02:42.380
That's my bad.
[ Chuckles ]

02:42.380 --> 02:44.420
It's why
it's called "training."

02:44.420 --> 02:48.830
Note to self --
triple-check name of deceased.

02:48.830 --> 02:51.330
Tony's dead.

02:51.330 --> 02:54.210
Tony is the one
that's dead.

02:54.210 --> 02:57.460
Dad's friend Tony
is gone forever.

02:57.460 --> 02:58.580
♪♪

02:58.580 --> 03:02.580
Tony -- dead Tony.

03:02.580 --> 03:04.670
R.I.P. Tony.

03:04.670 --> 03:06.620
Tony, Tony, Tony.

03:07.960 --> 03:10.330
Ruby: Whoo, here it is!

03:10.330 --> 03:13.420
Jesus truly is everywhere.

03:13.420 --> 03:15.830
Thank you for making this sweet
potato pie for me, Grandma.

03:15.830 --> 03:17.790
This is gonna kill
at the bake sale.
 Oh, honey!

03:17.790 --> 03:19.580
Bake sale?

03:19.580 --> 03:21.880
Wait. Why -- Why didn't you ask
me to make you something?

03:21.880 --> 03:24.250
It's a bake sale,
 not a bake throwaway.

03:24.250 --> 03:26.830
Oh, my God!
Grandma's pie!

03:26.830 --> 03:29.420
Diane! Diane!
Grandma's pie!

03:29.420 --> 03:30.880
Come look at Jesus.

03:30.880 --> 03:33.040
Okay, guys, guys.
This is Zoey's pie.

03:33.040 --> 03:34.460
But I can
make you a snack.

03:34.460 --> 03:35.670
Who wants celery?

03:35.670 --> 03:36.750
Is she serious?

03:36.750 --> 03:38.920
Mom, ask that again.

03:38.920 --> 03:40.380
Say it out loud.

03:40.380 --> 03:42.500
Okay, you know I can make things
other than celery, right?

03:42.500 --> 03:44.210
I can bake.
I can fry.

03:44.210 --> 03:48.000
I can use a, uh,
uh, a pressure cooker.

03:48.000 --> 03:49.120
Point to the toaster.

03:49.120 --> 03:50.540
The t--
 The toaster.
Where's the toaster?

03:50.540 --> 03:51.670
Th-- It is...
 Yep. Uh-huh.

03:51.670 --> 03:52.960
Hey, hey.
 She doesn't know where is.

03:52.960 --> 03:54.920
Mom's a working
anesthesiologist.

03:54.920 --> 03:57.170
She doesn't have time
to bake snack pies.

03:57.170 --> 03:58.080
Thank you, Zoey.

03:58.080 --> 03:59.500
Or do arts and crafts,

03:59.500 --> 04:01.500
or iron our clothes
adequately...
 What?

04:01.500 --> 04:03.830
...or make food that makes
people generally happy.

04:03.830 --> 04:05.330
Okay, that's enough,
that's enough, that's enough.

04:05.330 --> 04:07.710
No, I honestly think
it's cool

04:07.710 --> 04:09.330
that you don't know how
to do anything.
 What?!

04:09.330 --> 04:11.880
You're not asking the question
"Can women have it all?"

04:11.880 --> 04:12.830
You're answering.

04:12.830 --> 04:14.080
No. They can't.
 No.

04:14.080 --> 04:15.540
Really, Zoey?
 Yeah.

04:15.540 --> 04:17.209
Okay, fine.

04:17.209 --> 04:18.459
You know what?

04:18.459 --> 04:20.790
From now on, if you guys need
anything, ask me.

04:20.790 --> 04:22.710
Okay? Me.

04:22.710 --> 04:23.750
Got it.
 Rainbow: Okay.

04:23.750 --> 04:25.040
Um, Mom?
 Yes?

04:25.040 --> 04:26.790
Can you ask Grandma
to make some more pie?

04:26.790 --> 04:29.670
[ Ruby laughs ]

04:31.290 --> 04:33.830
Now, for anyone who's never
 been to a funeral in the hood,

04:33.830 --> 04:35.920
no one does it like we do.

04:35.920 --> 04:37.670
And that's probably
 a good thing.

04:37.670 --> 04:39.750
Tony Thompson...

04:39.750 --> 04:42.920
may your spirit soar high
like this dove.

04:42.920 --> 04:44.750
[ Wings flapping, thud ]

04:44.750 --> 04:47.500
[ People murmuring ]

04:47.500 --> 04:49.620
They could at least
turn the ceiling fan off.

04:49.620 --> 04:52.290
♪♪

04:52.290 --> 04:53.790
[ Ding! ]

04:53.790 --> 04:58.420
[ Voice breaking ]
♪ Let me lick you up and down ♪

04:58.420 --> 05:01.460
♪ Till you say stop ♪

05:01.460 --> 05:03.380
[ Sobbing ]

05:03.380 --> 05:07.540
♪ Let me play
with your body, baby ♪

05:07.540 --> 05:10.580
♪ Make you real hot ♪

05:10.580 --> 05:13.210
[ Wailing ] Oh! Why?!

05:15.750 --> 05:18.790
You sure know how
to stretch 35 bucks.

05:18.790 --> 05:21.170
Thank you, Sha.

05:21.170 --> 05:23.000
Mabel: Andre.
 Grandma!

05:23.000 --> 05:24.920
Pops didn't say
you were gonna be here.

05:24.920 --> 05:26.380
Oh, your father's
a heavy drinker, baby.

05:26.380 --> 05:27.500
[ Chuckles ]

05:27.500 --> 05:29.290
It's in the blood.
 Yes, it is.

05:29.290 --> 05:30.960
I pray for you, Dre.
 Mm-hmm.

05:30.960 --> 05:32.250
Bar's open.

05:32.250 --> 05:34.580
Ah, okay.
Don't get too happy, now.

05:34.580 --> 05:36.250
T Will: Hollywood Dre.

05:36.250 --> 05:39.880
T Will! Ah!
Good to see you, man.

05:39.880 --> 05:42.170
You looking clean, boy.
What kind of suit is that?

05:42.170 --> 05:43.750
Uh, well, you know,
I don't even know.

05:43.750 --> 05:44.500
Gucci?

05:44.500 --> 05:45.790
Uh...
 Damn!

05:45.790 --> 05:46.960
Look, man,
it was just a gift.

05:46.960 --> 05:48.540
Hey, hey, hey, hey,
how you doing?

05:48.540 --> 05:50.380
I'm great, man.
Just had twins.
 Oh!

05:50.380 --> 05:52.000
Well, not twins twins,

05:52.000 --> 05:53.830
but I did have two babies
at the same time

05:53.830 --> 05:55.000
from
two different women.

05:55.000 --> 05:56.420
That's kind of like twins.
 Right?

05:56.420 --> 05:58.120
I guess congratulations.

05:58.120 --> 05:59.460
Ha!

05:59.460 --> 06:00.830
Ledarius!
 [ Chuckles ]

06:00.830 --> 06:02.460
Come on, man.
Look at you.

06:02.460 --> 06:03.620
Aw,
you know I look awful.

06:03.620 --> 06:04.790
I wasn't gonna say it.

06:04.790 --> 06:06.250
Hey, man, what's going on?

06:06.250 --> 06:07.420
I can't call it, man,

06:07.420 --> 06:08.920
but I do got this
new cement business.

06:08.920 --> 06:10.290
I'm killing the hood
with it.

06:10.290 --> 06:11.880
I'm doing everything --

06:11.880 --> 06:14.000
sidewalks,
driveways, walkways,

06:14.000 --> 06:15.290
which are sidewalks
mixed with driveways.

06:15.290 --> 06:16.580
Did you know that?
 Okay.

06:16.580 --> 06:17.710
You know that new stadium
the Rams are building?

06:17.710 --> 06:18.670
Yeah.

06:18.670 --> 06:20.460
I'm not part of that.
 Ah.

06:20.460 --> 06:23.880
Ronnie! Mm!

06:23.880 --> 06:25.250
You didn't
want to dress up?

06:25.250 --> 06:27.420
I --
You are dressed up.

06:27.420 --> 06:29.380
Yeah, this is new.
 Yeah.

06:29.380 --> 06:32.170
And just like that,
 after too much time away,

06:32.170 --> 06:34.120
I was back with my crew.

06:34.120 --> 06:36.920
All:
♪ Let me lick you up and down ♪

06:36.920 --> 06:38.670
♪ Till you say stop ♪

06:38.670 --> 06:40.790
♪ Doo-o-o-o ♪

06:40.790 --> 06:43.830
♪ Let me play
with your body, baby ♪

06:43.830 --> 06:45.420
♪ Make you real hot ♪

06:45.420 --> 06:47.540
♪ Oo-o-h ♪
 Yeah, we got it!

06:47.540 --> 06:49.210
Well, on that one,
we got to go.

06:49.210 --> 06:50.620
[ Laughter ]

06:50.620 --> 06:51.830
Strong move
on them flowers, Dre.

06:51.830 --> 06:54.120
Oh, man. It was Tony.
Had to be done.

06:54.120 --> 06:55.670
Guess we'll see you
at the next funeral, Dre.

06:55.670 --> 06:56.880
Yeah,
let's be honest --

06:56.880 --> 06:58.540
it's probably gonna be
somebody from my family.

06:58.540 --> 06:59.960
Or me.

06:59.960 --> 07:01.080
Yeah, it's probably
gonna be you, dawg.

07:01.080 --> 07:02.380
You didn't have to say it
that fast.

07:02.380 --> 07:04.420
Okay, hey, look.

07:04.420 --> 07:06.500
I don't want to have to wait
till the next person's funeral.

07:06.500 --> 07:07.880
Next week...

07:07.880 --> 07:09.880
let's watch the game
at my house.
 Word?

07:09.880 --> 07:11.500
-Bring it through, man.
-All right. Cool.

07:11.500 --> 07:12.710
All right, let's do that.

07:12.710 --> 07:14.830
That's what we gonna do.
 Indeed.

07:14.830 --> 07:16.000
Barbecue going
and everything?

07:16.000 --> 07:17.500
Yeah, everything.
We cooking everything.

07:17.500 --> 07:19.330
[ Speaks indistinctly ]

07:19.330 --> 07:20.250
Yo, Dre.
 Mm?

07:20.250 --> 07:21.380
How was the repass?

07:21.380 --> 07:22.880
Oh, man, it was cool.
Thanks.

07:22.880 --> 07:25.210
You -- You?
I-I'll take this one.

07:25.210 --> 07:26.710
Uh, what's a "repass"?

07:26.710 --> 07:27.960
Are you kidding me
right now?

07:27.960 --> 07:29.670
It's when everybody
gets together

07:29.670 --> 07:31.500
after the funeral
with some food.

07:31.500 --> 07:32.920
Oh, a wake.
 Oh! A wake.

07:32.920 --> 07:34.580
Well,
we call it a repass.

07:34.580 --> 07:37.710
You guys just have to put rims
on everything, don't you?

07:37.710 --> 07:39.420
You know what?
I'm feeling too good right now

07:39.420 --> 07:41.830
to let you bring me down
with your daily dose of racism.

07:41.830 --> 07:43.080
I went home this weekend.

07:43.080 --> 07:44.120
Ohh.
 Wha?

07:44.120 --> 07:45.380
To the ghetto?

07:45.380 --> 07:46.710
You weren't scared?

07:46.710 --> 07:48.250
I went to a concert
once at The Forum

07:48.250 --> 07:50.120
and immediately canceled
all my credit cards.
 Yeah.

07:50.120 --> 07:52.380
Not gonna get to me,
because it was beautiful.

07:52.380 --> 07:55.210
And even better because I got
to help the family a little.

07:55.210 --> 07:58.380
Oh, you paid for the funeral.
That's very classy, Dre.

07:58.380 --> 07:59.880
And it's a tax write-off.

07:59.880 --> 08:01.170
Well, not all of it.

08:01.170 --> 08:02.960
Did you pay for half?
 Not quite.

08:02.960 --> 08:04.040
Charlie:
But you are gonna take care

08:04.040 --> 08:05.960
of the financial needs
of the widow, right?

08:05.960 --> 08:07.880
I bought the flowers.

08:07.880 --> 08:09.290
Good God, Dre.

08:09.290 --> 08:12.000
Flowers are just another thing
that will die on them.

08:12.000 --> 08:14.080
I guess I could've did
a little more.

08:14.080 --> 08:15.580
You got to step
your game up, Dre.

08:15.580 --> 08:18.290
Put your crew on your back.
Get your Kevin Garnett on.

08:18.290 --> 08:19.380
Said what?
 Soccer guy.

08:19.380 --> 08:21.330
Yep, my turn to bite.
My turn to bite.

08:21.330 --> 08:23.290
What exactly is
a "Kevin Garnett"?

08:23.290 --> 08:25.380
Kevin Garnett was
a very successful
black basketball player

08:25.380 --> 08:26.580
who played
for the Boston Celtics.

08:26.580 --> 08:27.960
It's always
a basketball player.

08:27.960 --> 08:29.120
Took care of his whole
childhood crew.

08:29.120 --> 08:31.290
Called themselves
the "O.B.F." --

08:31.290 --> 08:32.750
"Official Block Family."

08:32.750 --> 08:34.169
And in case
you're wondering --

08:34.169 --> 08:36.080
they're not accepting
no new members.

08:36.080 --> 08:38.289
A Black Celtic?

08:38.289 --> 08:39.789
Dre:
Charlie, you're right.

08:39.789 --> 08:41.169
I need
to start giving back,

08:41.169 --> 08:44.620
looking out for my crew,
because that's the dream.

08:44.620 --> 08:48.250
I can tell you without question
  that is not the dream.

08:48.250 --> 08:49.540
You wouldn't understand,

08:49.540 --> 08:51.540
because when you're the
successful one in your crew --

08:51.540 --> 08:53.380
Wait, wait, wait.
Wait one second. Okay.

08:53.380 --> 08:56.460
You're the successful one?
 Yeah.

08:56.460 --> 08:58.790
Did the bleachers collapse
at your graduation?

08:58.790 --> 09:00.040
[ Laughter ]
 Hey, hey, come on.

09:00.040 --> 09:01.330
They collapsed at mine.

09:01.330 --> 09:02.460
What?
 Hmm?

09:02.460 --> 09:04.210
Can't believe it's been
50 years already.

09:04.210 --> 09:06.790
Where does the time go?

09:06.790 --> 09:08.330
Charlie was right.

09:08.330 --> 09:11.790
I did need to step up,
 put my crew on my back.

09:11.790 --> 09:14.420
And what better place
 than my house?

09:14.420 --> 09:16.500
Hol-ly-wood!

09:16.500 --> 09:17.790
Nice place you got.
 Thanks, man.

09:17.790 --> 09:19.290
I mean, the patio's
a little uneven,

09:19.290 --> 09:20.830
but you knew that.

09:20.830 --> 09:23.380
Uh, I did not.

09:23.380 --> 09:24.750
Maybe you can fix it
for me.

09:24.750 --> 09:26.710
Yeah, man, that's
the great thing about cement --

09:26.710 --> 09:28.670
you can pretty much pour it
on anything.

09:28.670 --> 09:31.540
Damn, Dre.
This house is next level.

09:31.540 --> 09:32.880
How much is your rent?

09:32.880 --> 09:35.540
Uh, well, you know,
uh, normal house rent.

09:35.540 --> 09:37.580
Hey, man, can you
turn on the AC? It's a
little toasty in here.

09:37.580 --> 09:38.920
You could take
your hoodie off,

09:38.920 --> 09:40.580
but then we'll see
that weird thing on your neck.

09:40.580 --> 09:42.420
Okay, listen.
I told you it was nothing.

09:42.420 --> 09:43.580
I mean,
what are odds of cancer

09:43.580 --> 09:44.830
hitting four people
in one family?

09:44.830 --> 09:46.380
Dre: Hey, you know what?
Bow will look at that.

09:46.380 --> 09:47.500
She's got nothing else
better to do.

09:47.500 --> 09:49.920
Bow!
Jack's hurt! It's bad!

09:49.920 --> 09:51.580
What happened?
What happened?!

09:51.580 --> 09:53.170
No, no, no.
He's fine. He's fine!

09:53.170 --> 09:55.960
I just need you to look
at Ronnie's neck.
 What?!

09:55.960 --> 09:58.620
Baby, please don't embarrass me
in front of my friends, okay?

09:58.620 --> 10:00.460
Ronnie doesn't have a doctor
and he needs your help.

10:00.460 --> 10:01.880
Oh, and where's
the checkbook?

10:01.880 --> 10:03.750
Ledarius, he's gonna
cement the patio.

10:03.750 --> 10:05.790
You know what? Can you guys
just excuse us for one second?

10:05.790 --> 10:07.750
I just want to tell Dre
how much I love him.

10:07.750 --> 10:10.040
Oh, I love you,
too, baby.
 [ Laughs ] I do,
'cause I love you,

10:10.040 --> 10:12.460
and about how much I love
all his choices, and...

10:12.460 --> 10:13.710
Right here, right?
 Yeah, this is --

10:13.710 --> 10:15.580
Yeah, yeah, yeah.
This is insane.

10:15.580 --> 10:19.000
I'm Kevin Garnett,
and they are my O.B.F.

10:19.000 --> 10:20.540
T Will: Yo, Dre,
this TV is crazy!

10:20.540 --> 10:21.540
It's yours!

10:21.540 --> 10:22.880
N-- Wha--

10:22.880 --> 10:24.460
Dre, what are you doing?

10:24.460 --> 10:27.250
I'm saving my crew,
damn it!

10:27.250 --> 10:30.670
♪♪

10:34.880 --> 10:35.880
Are you sure?
 Yeah.

10:35.880 --> 10:37.290
Wow! Good
looking out, Dre.

10:37.290 --> 10:39.420
Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey.

10:39.420 --> 10:40.620
Huh? What?
 Was that my bike?

10:40.620 --> 10:41.620
Was it?

10:41.620 --> 10:43.330
Yes! I love that bike.

10:43.330 --> 10:44.670
Bow, you never ride it.

10:44.670 --> 10:47.710
Because I'm pregnant,
and it's been raining.

10:47.710 --> 10:48.830
Make up your mind, Bow.

10:48.830 --> 10:50.920
Either you're pregnant
or it's raining.

10:50.920 --> 10:53.330
Dre, why are you giving away
all of our things?

10:53.330 --> 10:54.830
We can get more things.

10:54.830 --> 10:56.500
I can't get more friends.

10:56.500 --> 10:57.920
They need my help.

10:57.920 --> 10:59.170
Well, if this is
so important to you,

10:59.170 --> 11:00.290
why have you
never done it before?

11:00.290 --> 11:01.880
Because Tony has
never died before.

11:01.880 --> 11:03.380
Oh, okay.

11:03.380 --> 11:05.330
Except for 45 minutes
in high school.
 What?

11:05.330 --> 11:07.000
That's when we started
calling him Zombie T.

11:07.000 --> 11:09.880
But he's never died
and stayed died.
 Oh, my God.

11:09.880 --> 11:11.750
This is a wake-up call,
Bow.

11:11.750 --> 11:13.790
I-I'm making up
for lost time.

11:13.790 --> 11:16.460
Okay, your heart is
in the right place, Dre,

11:16.460 --> 11:18.790
but you can't save
everybody.

11:18.790 --> 11:20.170
[ Doorbell rings ]
 Yeah --

11:23.120 --> 11:25.620
Oh.
 Oh, Grandma Mabel.
Come on in.

11:25.620 --> 11:28.460
Well, hi!
What are you doing here?

11:28.460 --> 11:30.040
I don't know.
 Oh.

11:30.040 --> 11:32.040
I was watching my stories.
 Mm-hmm?

11:32.040 --> 11:34.920
This man driving a car
with a pink moustache

11:34.920 --> 11:37.580
told me I needed to pack
my things and get over here.

11:37.580 --> 11:39.120
He looked like
he meant business.
 Huh.

11:39.120 --> 11:40.380
So here I am.

11:40.380 --> 11:42.960
I sent him, Grandma.
You're safe now.

11:42.960 --> 11:45.460
Now, come on, Grandma. I'm gonna
lay you down on this couch

11:45.460 --> 11:46.540
and bring you
some hot food.

11:46.540 --> 11:48.330
But I'm not hungry.

11:48.330 --> 11:49.830
I know, Grandma.

11:49.830 --> 11:51.500
I'll be right back.

11:51.500 --> 11:53.000
Look at her.

11:53.000 --> 11:54.750
Poor thing ain't ate
in so long

11:54.750 --> 11:56.080
she doesn't even know
when she's hungry.

11:56.080 --> 11:57.330
Seriously, Dre?

11:57.330 --> 11:59.040
I had to take her
out of that neighborhood, Bow.

11:59.040 --> 12:02.040
She needs me. They need me.
You wouldn't understand.

12:02.040 --> 12:07.080
I understand that I have
your fifth child in my belly,

12:07.080 --> 12:08.790
and I have no backup plan.

12:08.790 --> 12:10.670
Mnh, baby. Baby, baby, baby,
don't listen to her,

12:10.670 --> 12:12.580
'cause she doesn't
understand.

12:12.580 --> 12:14.920
This is your family.
You help them however you can.

12:14.920 --> 12:16.330
Thank you, Ma.

12:16.330 --> 12:17.380
Mm-hmm, Mm-hmm.
 Oh, seriously.

12:17.380 --> 12:18.750
But I hope you're not
giving them money.

12:18.750 --> 12:20.920
Mnh-mnh.
Stick to the hard goods.

12:20.920 --> 12:24.080
No receipts 'cause they'll just
return it for cash.

12:24.080 --> 12:25.540
They're animals.

12:25.540 --> 12:28.080
Mabel, what
are you doing here?

12:28.080 --> 12:28.830
Mabel: I don't know.

12:28.830 --> 12:30.580
♪♪

12:30.580 --> 12:33.460
Okay, I think we're good.
Come on. Hurry, hurry.

12:33.460 --> 12:34.620
So,
Grandma's downstairs.

12:34.620 --> 12:36.500
Her sewing machine
is in the garage.

12:36.500 --> 12:37.500
Diane: Got it.

12:37.500 --> 12:38.380
Rainbow: Hey, guys.
 Hey!

12:38.380 --> 12:39.580
What are you guys doing?

12:39.580 --> 12:40.670
Nothing.

12:40.670 --> 12:43.500
Just some big-sister,
little-sister bonding.

12:43.500 --> 12:45.670
Cut the crap.
What's that behind your back?

12:45.670 --> 12:48.710
Oh, um, just a paper.
Just a paper.
 Oh, my God.

12:48.710 --> 12:50.120
Oh, look at that --

12:50.120 --> 12:52.620
"Help your kids make a costume
for carbohydrate day."

12:52.620 --> 12:54.540
[ Laughs ]
Do you need a costume?

12:54.540 --> 12:55.330
No, she just wa--

12:55.330 --> 12:57.880
Quiet!
I'm asking Diane.

12:57.880 --> 13:00.500
Diane,
do you need a costume?

13:00.500 --> 13:04.080
I need to be a potato.
It's mandatory.

13:04.080 --> 13:06.040
Why? I don't know.

13:06.040 --> 13:08.880
Oh, well, why didn't you ask
your mommy for help, sweetie?

13:08.880 --> 13:10.540
Don't look at Zoey.
Look at me.

13:10.540 --> 13:12.960
Did you need a costume?

13:15.040 --> 13:15.790
Mommy...

13:15.790 --> 13:17.210
Yes?

13:17.210 --> 13:19.880
...can you please
make me a potato costume?

13:19.880 --> 13:22.210
I would love to!

13:22.210 --> 13:23.290
When do you need it by?

13:23.290 --> 13:24.040
Tomorrow morning.

13:24.040 --> 13:25.750
Ooh! Okay.

13:25.750 --> 13:27.620
Wow, that's the next morning
happening.

13:27.620 --> 13:29.120
I can't order anything
online.

13:29.120 --> 13:30.290
You don't need to do it.

13:30.290 --> 13:31.830
No! I want to do it.

13:31.830 --> 13:33.500
[ Chuckling ]
I want to do it, okay?

13:33.500 --> 13:34.540
It's no problem.

13:34.540 --> 13:36.330
I've got this.
I'm here for you.

13:36.330 --> 13:37.960
I'm gonna make you a potato!

13:37.960 --> 13:39.000
Mommy's got this.

13:39.000 --> 13:40.620
[ Laughs ] I got it.

13:40.620 --> 13:43.710
This is gonna go bad
for you.

13:43.710 --> 13:46.380
"Operation Save the Hood"
 was on --

13:46.380 --> 13:48.580
so many people to save,
 so little time.

13:48.580 --> 13:50.920
Which is why I stopped
 to pick up Sha

13:50.920 --> 13:53.710
and get breakfast, lunch,
 and dinner all at once.

13:53.710 --> 13:54.710
Then we got to work...

13:54.710 --> 13:56.120
[ Both snoring ]

13:56.120 --> 13:58.000
...after a short nap.

13:58.000 --> 14:00.960
I got T Will some diapers
 for his version of twins...

14:00.960 --> 14:02.670
[ Ding! ]
  ...who were more twins
 than I thought.

14:02.670 --> 14:05.830
The moms were sisters
 who were twins.

14:05.830 --> 14:07.290
Then it was Ronnie's turn.

14:07.290 --> 14:08.750
Not only did I get

14:08.750 --> 14:10.790
his surprisingly benign
 tumor removed,

14:10.790 --> 14:12.790
I also got him a vasectomy,

14:12.790 --> 14:15.540
'cause let's be honest,
 his genes are toxic.

14:15.540 --> 14:18.790
After Ledarius "fixed"
 my patio,

14:18.790 --> 14:21.540
I realized his cement work
 might not be five-star.

14:21.540 --> 14:23.330
Whoa!
 [ Body thuds ]

14:23.330 --> 14:25.250
So I got him a job.

14:25.250 --> 14:28.330
I was like Robin Hood,
 but I wasn't stealing.

14:28.330 --> 14:30.120
So I guess I was just a hero --

14:30.120 --> 14:33.540
hero, friend, handsome bastard.

14:33.540 --> 14:37.960
[ Gasps ] Ooh!
There's my little potato!

14:37.960 --> 14:40.540
Hi! Oh, goodness!

14:40.540 --> 14:43.790
Don't you just love
the imperfect simpleness

14:43.790 --> 14:45.080
of a homemade costume?

14:45.080 --> 14:46.420
I do not.

14:46.420 --> 14:48.750
Oh, come on, honey.
You're so silly.

14:48.750 --> 14:51.210
This is what happens
when you ask Mommy to help you.

14:51.210 --> 14:53.580
And now, for my encore,

14:53.580 --> 14:56.920
I am gonna help Jack
make a Popsicle-stick pueblo.

14:56.920 --> 14:58.750
Ha!
What the hell's a pueblo?

14:58.750 --> 15:00.620
I don't really know.

15:00.620 --> 15:02.330
Junior:
Something on your mind,

15:02.330 --> 15:04.000
something you'd like
to talk about?

15:04.000 --> 15:05.330
Look, save it.

15:05.330 --> 15:07.120
I'm not weak like the rest
of the family.

15:07.120 --> 15:08.580
Weak?
 Mm-hmm.

15:08.580 --> 15:09.920
I'd say it takes strength

15:09.920 --> 15:12.500
to wear one of Mom's
costumes to school.

15:12.500 --> 15:16.040
The humiliation alone
would break most people.

15:16.040 --> 15:17.920
[ Scoffs ] Not me.
I was fine.

15:17.920 --> 15:19.880
Really?
Kids can be pretty mean

15:19.880 --> 15:21.960
with the teasing
and the whispering

15:21.960 --> 15:23.330
and the name-calling.

15:23.330 --> 15:24.420
[ Sighs ]

15:24.420 --> 15:26.170
[ Whispers ] What
did they call you?

15:26.170 --> 15:29.420
Nothing.

15:29.420 --> 15:31.330
What did they call you,
Diane?

15:33.580 --> 15:37.830
[ Voice breaking ]
They called me "Poo-tato"!

15:37.830 --> 15:40.210
♪♪

15:40.210 --> 15:42.830
Yes, they did.

15:42.830 --> 15:45.080
So, I was hanging out
 with my crew again,

15:45.080 --> 15:48.420
and I knew they appreciated
 everything I did for them.

15:48.420 --> 15:49.920
So, how are those diapers
working out for you?

15:49.920 --> 15:52.170
Nice, right?
 Uh, yeah.

15:52.170 --> 15:53.790
You know, like diapers.

15:53.790 --> 15:56.380
Cool. No doubt.
Life-changing.

15:56.380 --> 15:58.420
Hey, Ronnie.
Yo, how's that snip, man?

15:58.420 --> 16:00.330
Still working out?
 Uh, I guess.

16:00.330 --> 16:02.120
What are you asking me,
Dre?

16:02.120 --> 16:04.170
Nothing, you know, just making
sure I took care of you,

16:04.170 --> 16:05.420
'cause you know
that's what I do, right?

16:07.040 --> 16:08.420
Hey, look
at that waitress.
 Hmm?

16:08.420 --> 16:09.620
She's sexy as hell,
right?

16:09.620 --> 16:12.120
Yeah, but you know
what else is sexy?

16:12.120 --> 16:13.580
Generosity.

16:13.580 --> 16:15.620
You mean, like,
sexual generosity?

16:16.790 --> 16:17.790
That is hella sexy.

16:17.790 --> 16:18.790
[ Laughter ]

16:18.790 --> 16:20.500
No, I mean...

16:20.500 --> 16:24.120
generosity like taking care
of those you came up with.

16:24.120 --> 16:25.120
Dre, what's up
with you, man?

16:25.120 --> 16:25.920
What?

16:25.920 --> 16:27.540
No, man. Dre's right.

16:27.540 --> 16:30.120
Let's raise 'em up...
to a great friend,

16:30.120 --> 16:31.960
and the most generous man
we've ever known.

16:31.960 --> 16:33.420
Man, come on.

16:33.420 --> 16:35.040
To a guy who's made
all our lives better.

16:35.040 --> 16:36.290
To Tony!

16:36.290 --> 16:38.420
Tony!
 Tony!

16:38.420 --> 16:40.750
To Tony?
[Bleep] Tony.

16:40.750 --> 16:42.210
Mm.

16:42.210 --> 16:43.830
Did Tony buy you diapers,
huh?

16:43.830 --> 16:46.460
Or get you a job?
O-Or fix your disgusting neck?

16:46.460 --> 16:49.120
Tony ain't did nothing
but die in his sleep.

16:49.120 --> 16:50.040
Whoa.

16:50.040 --> 16:51.920
Damn, Hollywood.

16:51.920 --> 16:53.080
You really on one.

16:53.080 --> 16:55.540
I think it's best
if we just walk away.

16:55.540 --> 16:58.170
♪♪

17:01.420 --> 17:03.250
No, no, no, no, no!
I'll get it...

17:03.250 --> 17:05.119
like I get everything!

17:09.079 --> 17:10.329
Hey.
So, how's it coming?

17:10.329 --> 17:12.079
Fine.
 It doesn't look fine.

17:12.079 --> 17:13.619
Did you put in
a solid foundation?

17:13.619 --> 17:16.540
Of course I put in
a solid foundation, Ruby.

17:16.540 --> 17:18.170
Pack it up.
Get out the pueblo.

17:18.170 --> 17:20.750
You made four squares
for your base.

17:20.750 --> 17:22.040
Yeah.
 Uh-huh.

17:22.040 --> 17:24.119
Mm-hmm.

17:24.119 --> 17:26.290
[ Glass thuds ]
 Oh, God! [ Screams ]

17:26.290 --> 17:31.170
Don't you ever lie to me again
about a four-square base.

17:31.170 --> 17:33.420
[ Sighs ]
 Oh, Lord.

17:34.750 --> 17:37.000
Why do you
do this to yourself?

17:37.000 --> 17:39.420
Sweetheart, listen.

17:39.420 --> 17:43.040
As a mom, you just want
to prove to your kids

17:43.040 --> 17:45.120
that you can
do everything.

17:45.120 --> 17:48.790
Mom, remember when Derek
broke up with me?
 Yeah.

17:48.790 --> 17:52.000
Or when I needed help
with my college essay?
 [ Chuckling ] Yeah.

17:52.000 --> 17:53.540
Or when I needed help
with anything

17:53.540 --> 17:55.750
that really matters
in my life?
 Mm.

17:55.750 --> 18:00.580
You don't have to do everything
to be everything to us.

18:00.580 --> 18:03.170
Oh, sweetheart.

18:03.170 --> 18:04.540
Thank you.

18:04.540 --> 18:07.250
So, really,
please, just stop.

18:07.250 --> 18:10.420
Because, I mean, seriously, if
Diane becomes a super villain,

18:10.420 --> 18:12.120
"Poo-tato" is why.

18:12.120 --> 18:14.750
[ Both laugh ]

18:16.500 --> 18:18.960
So, I had lost my crew

18:18.960 --> 18:21.710
and spit on the grave
 of a dear friend.

18:21.710 --> 18:24.750
But they forced my hand
 with their ingratitude,

18:24.750 --> 18:27.960
so I turned to help those
 I knew who would be grateful.

18:27.960 --> 18:30.710
Why am I still here?

18:30.710 --> 18:32.460
'Cause I'm saving you.

18:32.460 --> 18:35.250
Look, you don't ever have
to go back to the hood, Grandma.

18:35.250 --> 18:37.170
And I'm this close
to selling your house.

18:37.170 --> 18:40.000
Are you crazy?
You can't sell my house.

18:40.000 --> 18:41.210
That's my house.

18:41.210 --> 18:42.790
This is better.

18:42.790 --> 18:44.710
Look, I'll put you Encino.
You'll love it.

18:44.710 --> 18:46.830
Plus,
they got a Sizzler here.

18:46.830 --> 18:49.540
I'm fine where I am.

18:49.540 --> 18:52.540
My friends are nearby,
I know all my channels,

18:52.540 --> 18:54.790
and I'm right next to the ATM
where my money's at.

18:54.790 --> 18:56.790
Boy, take me home.

18:56.790 --> 18:57.880
Yes, ma'am.

18:59.170 --> 19:01.040
[ Door closes ]

19:02.710 --> 19:03.750
What are you guys
doing here?

19:03.750 --> 19:04.790
Came to give you back
your stuff.

19:05.920 --> 19:07.120
Where's the back wheel?

19:07.120 --> 19:08.540
You gave it to me
like this.

19:08.540 --> 19:09.540
What?

19:09.540 --> 19:11.000
Oh, all right, Dre.

19:11.000 --> 19:12.830
I'll get you another
little back wheel.

19:12.830 --> 19:13.920
How much does it cost?
Never mind.

19:13.920 --> 19:15.420
You gave it to me
like this.

19:15.420 --> 19:17.080
Hey, Dre, we don't need
your handouts, bro.

19:17.080 --> 19:18.920
Hold up, man.

19:18.920 --> 19:20.670
Y'all making me out
to be the bad guy

19:20.670 --> 19:22.460
because I'm trying to help
better people's lives?

19:22.460 --> 19:24.290
Hold on.
We're good, man.

19:24.290 --> 19:25.960
Yeah, man,
I got my cement thing,

19:25.960 --> 19:27.920
and T Will's good
with them babies.
 I am.

19:27.920 --> 19:29.460
I mean, don't get me wrong,
he is a bad guy.

19:29.460 --> 19:30.620
A bad dude.
 One of the worst.

19:30.620 --> 19:32.750
All right, yes,
they were sisters.

19:32.750 --> 19:34.830
Yes, I sexed them
against each other,

19:34.830 --> 19:36.920
and, yes, I tore
a whole family apart.

19:36.920 --> 19:38.000
But what's that say
about me?

19:39.040 --> 19:40.540
I'm great at sex.

19:41.670 --> 19:42.960
And he's a good daddy.

19:42.960 --> 19:44.500
Thank you, big homey.

19:44.500 --> 19:46.880
See, look, we're good.
We don't need your stuff.

19:46.880 --> 19:48.670
We just want
to be your boys, man.

19:48.670 --> 19:50.710
Hey, man, I want
to be your boy, too.

19:50.710 --> 19:53.670
But sometimes I feel bad because
I'm the one that made it out.

19:53.670 --> 19:57.170
What you're experiencing
is called Survivor's Remorse.

19:57.170 --> 19:59.620
Survivor's Remorse?
That sounds stupid.

19:59.620 --> 20:01.670
If you wouldn't mind
signing my grief log,

20:01.670 --> 20:02.750
I'd be happy
to explain it to --

20:02.750 --> 20:04.540
Junior! Get out!

20:04.540 --> 20:06.120
Okay, I get it.

20:06.120 --> 20:08.540
You're lashing out
because you're all feeling sad

20:08.540 --> 20:12.420
about Tony -- dead Tony.

20:16.420 --> 20:17.580
Okay.
You know what?

20:17.580 --> 20:19.670
I-I-I'm gonna give you guys
some time.

20:19.670 --> 20:22.420
I'll leave this right here
in case you're ready to sign.

20:22.420 --> 20:23.790
Thank y--

20:23.790 --> 20:28.500
Look, fellas, I'm sorry
I've been acting crazy lately.

20:28.500 --> 20:31.250
And I'm gonna try to stop
giving you all stuff.

20:31.250 --> 20:32.250
Whoa, whoa.

20:32.250 --> 20:33.710
Y-You mean moving forward,
right,

20:33.710 --> 20:35.790
like, post-today?

20:35.790 --> 20:37.460
'C-Cause all this
is ours.

20:37.460 --> 20:39.080
Yeah, this is more
of a symbolic gesture.

20:39.080 --> 20:41.830
Yeah, something to begin
the healing process.

20:41.830 --> 20:43.380
You can just...

20:43.380 --> 20:45.750
gradually give it to us,
you know?

20:45.750 --> 20:47.580
You don't need to stop...
 Love the bike!

20:47.580 --> 20:50.000
...so fast.

20:50.000 --> 20:52.040
♪♪

20:56.420 --> 20:57.830
So, I was back with my boys,

20:57.830 --> 21:00.460
and it felt good.

21:00.460 --> 21:04.330
Because we were a crew,
 and that's for life.

21:04.330 --> 21:08.000
And the fact is, tomorrow's not
 promised to any of us,

21:08.000 --> 21:10.960
so you want to spend
 as much time as you can

21:10.960 --> 21:13.040
with the people you care about,

21:13.040 --> 21:16.170
'cause you never know
 who may be gone too soon.

21:16.170 --> 21:19.040
[ Indistinct talking ]
